SUMMARY:A Red Carpet Affair 2020 Year of The Nurse Documentary by Robyn Ro
 ots MSN\, RN\, CDN
LOCATION:2511 East Columbus Drive Tampa \, FL 33605 United States
DESCRIPTION:This distinguished event is held in honor of National Nurses W
 eek and Mental Health Awareness Month\, recognizing the unwavering dedicat
 ion\, compassion\, and resilience of nurses and healthcare providers who s
 erve with excellence. It is our goal to celebrate their commitment to heal
 ing\, advocacy\, and whole-person care while also elevating mental health 
 as a shared community priority. As part of our commitment to holistic well
 ness\, a licensed mental health care professional will be on site to provi
 de support\, answer questions\, and assist with navigation to resources as
  needed. Additionally\, we plan to invite local nursing schools\, colleges
 \, universities\, and technical programs to participate as vendors\, offer
 ing free educational tables to share information and inspire the next gene
 ration of healthcare professionals. This red-carpet experience will also f
 eature a special presentation of the documentary\, 2020 Year of the Nurse\
 , written\, produced\, and directed by Robyn Roots\, MSN\, RN\, CDN\, high
 lighting the powerful storiesand impact of nurses across the nation. Attir
 e Green andor White \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.gov/node/189396
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/189396
END:VEVENT
