SUMMARY:Surface and Fire  Raku Firing
LOCATION:120 W Gasparilla Plaza Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:This four-week workshop immerses students in the bold forms an
 d graphic surfaces that define Jun Kanekos iconic ceramic practice\, with 
 participants creating sculptural pieces no larger than eight inches cubed.
  Over the first three weeks at the Tampa Museum of Art\, students will con
 struct smaller-scale works and apply raku-specific glazes with an emphasis
  on mark-making\, pattern\, and architectural presence. The workshop culmi
 nates in an exhilarating fourth week at the City of Tampa Golding Art Stud
 io\, where participants will fire their pieces in the raku tradition\, pul
 ling glowing ceramics from the kiln and witnessing the dramatic transforma
 tions of post-fire reduction. Drawing inspiration from Kanekos monumental 
 approach while working at an accessible scale\, this course invites both b
 eginners and experienced ceramicists to explore the dynamic relationship b
 etween form\, surface\, and fire. Wednesdays\, Jun 3  24  6:00 9:00 PM (4 
 classes) Ages 18  Beginner-Intermediate Level \n\nPermalink: https://www.t
 ampa.gov/node/188656
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/188656
END:VEVENT
